Uttar Pradesh
Aug 25, 2014
Domestic Violence, Dowry Harassment, Other
Description:
			Body of a 25-year-old woman was found hanging from the ceiling of her residence under Manjhanpur Kotwali of Kaushambi on Sunday morning. Her parents later lodged an FIR alleging that her daughter was killed and hanged by her husband and in-laws for dowry.

Later, the police lodged a case under the Dowry Act and sent the body for post mortem. Police said that investigations were underway and the post mortem report would reveal the exact cause of death. "We are waiting for post mortem report to ascertain the cause of death," said the police.

According to police, Shilpi was married to Rakesh Kumar of Nehru Nagar about six months back. Her parents claimed at her husband and in-laws were demanding Rs 2 lakh in cash. They even tortured her in order to force her parents to fulfill their demands. She had repeatedly informed her parents about the torture.

Her parents further alleged that Shilpi's in-laws and husband had even threatened her of dire consequences, if she failed to fulfill their demands.